Live Stream Segmenter - Dual License Notice
============================================

This project contains software licensed under different licenses depending on
the component. The applicable license for each component is indicated in the
file headers.

Overall License Structure
-------------------------

The project is licensed under a dual license model:

1. GNU General Public License v3.0 or later (GPL-3.0-or-later)
2. MIT License

Which License Applies Where
----------------------------

### GPL-3.0-or-later Licensed Components

The following components are licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0
or later. See LICENSE.GPL-3.0-or-later for the full license text.

- Main plugin integration code (src/plugin-main.cpp)
- OBS Bridge utilities (src/BridgeUtils/*)
- UI components (src/LiveStreamSegmenter/UI/*)

These components interact directly with OBS Studio, which is licensed under
GPL-2.0-or-later, and therefore must be GPL-compatible.

### MIT Licensed Components

The following components are licensed under the MIT License. See LICENSE.MIT
for the full license text.

- Logger framework (src/Logger/*)
- cURL helper utilities (src/CurlHelper/*)
- Update checker (src/UpdateChecker/*)
- YouTube API components (src/LiveStreamSegmenter/API/*)
- Google OAuth2 and authentication components (src/LiveStreamSegmenter/Auth/*)

These components are designed to be reusable in other projects and are licensed
under the permissive MIT License to enable broader use.

How to Determine Which License Applies
---------------------------------------

Each source file in this project contains a header comment that explicitly
states which license applies to that file. Look for one of these statements:

- "This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it
  under the terms of the GNU General Public License..." indicates GPL-3.0-or-later
  
- "This software is licensed under the MIT License." indicates MIT License

License Files
-------------

The complete text of each license can be found in the following files:

- LICENSE.GPL-3.0-or-later - Full text of the GNU GPL v3.0
- LICENSE.MIT - Full text of the MIT License

